cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.ST

This paper deals with machine learning algorithms and specifically focuses on boosting decision trees. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses calibration methods for improving the accuracy of predicted probabilities, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments with boosting weak models such as decision stumps and more complex models such as full decision trees, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
